    "body": "### Problem\n\nAny Ncurses app that [`init_color`](https://invisible-island.net/ncurses/man/curs_color.3x.html) displays colors incorrectly when run under the terminal-buffer. Additionally,  it should be noted that the same **exact** coloring-issue happens to appear under a `tmux`-session *(when and **only**)* when there's no `$TERM` defaulting to: `xterm-256color`,`alacritty`, etc. \n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n\n|✅ Alacritty| ❌ Neovim| ❌ tmux | ✅ tmux + $TERM |\n| :---: | :---: | :---: | :---: |\n| [![enter image description here][1]][1]| [![enter image description here][2]][2] | [![enter image description here][2]][2] | [![enter image description here][1]][1]|\n\n\n```c\n/* \n * Simply `gcc ./tst_vim_terminal_buffer_ncurses_color_init.cpp -lncurses`\n * and then run `./a.out` inside `:terminal`, a tmux session, plain terminal etc.\n*/\n\n#include <ncurses.h>\n\nint main()\n{\t\n\tinitscr();     // Start curses mode \t\t  \n\tstart_color(); // Start color  mode\n\n\t// initialize  colors\n\tinit_color(8 , 900, 900 , 0); // yellow\n\tinit_color(9 , 0, 1000 , 80); // green\n\tinit_color(10, 700 , 0, 900); // purple\n\n\t// initialize pairs of colors (fg, bg)\n\tinit_pair(1, 8, COLOR_BLACK);\n\tinit_pair(2, 9, COLOR_BLACK);\n\tinit_pair(3,10, COLOR_BLACK);\n\n  // using those colors\n  for (int i=1; i<4; ++i){\n\t  attron(COLOR_PAIR(i));\n\t  printw(\"Hello World !!!\\n\");\n\t  attroff(COLOR_PAIR(i));\n\t}\n\trefresh(); // Print it on to the real screen \n\tgetch  (); // Wait for user input \n\tendwin (); // End curses mode\t\t  \n\n\treturn 0;\n}\n```\n\n<sub> *(Or simply, you may recreate the issue using this [tui-app](https://github.com/GiorgosXou/TUIFIManager) with [custom theming](https://github.com/GiorgosXou/our-tuifi-themes))* </sub>\n\n\n  [1]: https://i.sstatic.net/A2Hb4BD8.jpg\n  [2]: https://i.sstatic.net/b0J9w6Ur.jpg\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIt should show the proper colors\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.11.5\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nyes, 9.1.1908\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux x86_64\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\n(Any terminal)\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\n(xterm-256color, alacritty, etc.)\n\n### Installation\n\nsudo pacman -S neovim",
