            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "On my system, it's using OSC 4 and OSC 104 to change palette colors and reset palette colors respectively. nvim doesn't handle those OSC commands. One solution is to send those commands to the host TTY using a TermRequest autocmd that runs `nvim_ui_send` (though OSC 104 is not presently generating a TermRequest event). However, it might be preferred to handle those OSC codes directly in the terminal implementation; I'm not sure.",
